@page
@model AboutModel

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About";
}
<link href="~/Content/MvcGrid/mvc-grid.css" rel="stylesheet">

<div style="margin-bottom:5px">
    Snortnet is a powerful web interface for Snort log analysis. Application is build upon a self-contained .NET Core runtime and contains a built-in web server.
    Web features: 
</div>
<div>
    <a href="/Index" target="_blank">Dashboard</a>
    – Shows the latest threads on the interactive timeline and most common source/destination hosts and attack signatures from the selected time interval.
    </br>
    <a href="/Events" target="_blank">Events</a>
    – Shows all Snort alerts sorted by the most recent ones. Table can be filtered and these filters can be saved globally and applied to all graphs under "Statistics" tab.
    </br>
    <a href="/Events" target="_blank">Detail</a>
    – Shows packet associated with specific attack. Allows pcap (requires libpcap) and readable (requires Tcpdump installed) export options.
    Last bottom table shows Wireshark-like output (requires Tshark installed).
    </br>
    <a href="/Protocols" target="_blank">Protocols</a>
    – Pictures the most common source and destination ports used for attacks.
    </br>
    <a href="/Endpoints" target="_blank">Endpoints</a>
    – Pictures the most common source and destination IP adresses used for attacks.
    </br>
    <a href="/Signatures" target="_blank">Signatures</a>
    – Pictures the most common signatures used for attacks.
    </br>
    <a href="/Origin" target="_blank">Origin</a>
    – Pictures the most common states of origin associated with attacks on a worldwide map.
    </br>
</div>
